org.cripac.isee.vpe.ctrl

Class TaskData.ExecutionPlan

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cripac.isee.vpe.ctrl.TaskData.ExecutionPlan
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Enclosing class:
    TaskData<T extends java.io.Serializable>

    public static class TaskData.ExecutionPlan
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    The ExecutionPlan class represents a directed acyclic graph of the execution flows of modules. Each node is an execution of a module. Each link represents that an execution should output to a next execution node. One module may exist multiple times in a graph.
    Author:
    Ken Yu, CRIPAC, 2016
